> **Theory Box: How RAG Works**
>
> RAG combines the *retrieval* power of embeddings with the *generation* power of LLMs. The vector database finds relevant chunks using semantic similarity. Those chunks get injected into the prompt, giving the LLM accurate, specific context it was never trained on. RAG is the most common way to give LLMs access to private/current data.

